.TH "psc_dma_trigger" 9 "psc_dma_trigger" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
psc_dma_trigger \- start and stop the DMA transfer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" psc_dma_trigger
.BI "(struct snd_soc_component *component "  ","
.BI "struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ","
.BI "int cmd "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "component" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "substream" 12
-- undescribed --
.IP "cmd" 12
-- undescribed --
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

This function is called by ALSA to start, stop, pause, and resume the DMA
transfer of data.
